    "121363539": {
      "title": "Triangulated graphs and the elimination process",
      "abstract": "Abstract A triangulated graph is a graph in which for every cycle of length l > 3, there is an edge joining two nonconsecutive vertices. In this paper we study triangulated graphs and show that they play an important role in the elimination process. The results have application in the study of the numerical solution of sparse positive definite systems of linear equations by Gaussian elimination."
    }
